</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/udanaellebladesong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Danaelle Bladesong</A> at: 4/8/02 9:16:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uparticleboy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>particleboy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/10/02 12:21:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=586.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Beggars</span><hr size=1> At different times my druid was driven to distraction by beggars for buffs, ports, money, whatever.  But there is one thing people can beg me for that I will ALWAYS give if I have and I have the time... and thats information.<br>
<br>
What despairs me about the beggars is they want &quot;stuff&quot;... plat, buffs, items.  Things to make their life easier without them having to apply themselves.<br>
<br>
However if I get a tell out of the blue (which occasionally happens) like:<br>
<br>
- &quot;Can you please tell me how evade works?&quot;<br>
- &quot;Do you have any suggestions for equipment I might get at level X with Y pp?&quot;<br>
- &quot;Can I trouble you for some advice on where to hunt at level X?&quot;<br>
...etc...<br>
<br>
then I'll happily answer.  What is the old saying?  Give a man a fish and you feed him for a day, teach him how to fish and you feed him for a lifetime.  Information I will always give, items/buffs/plat I will never (rarely) give.<br>
<br>
I'm reminded of an interview I read of some guy who'd made many millions of dollars as an entrepeneur.  He was despairing at one aspect of it: people he knew from a long time ago would come out of the woodwork and ask for money.  It would also change some people around him.  But what most surprised him was how few people ever asked him HOW he made his money.<br>
<br>
You see the same thing in EQ: people don't want to apply themselves, put in an effort or learn.  They want instant gratification for zero effort.<br>
<br>
Call me ebay too cos I didn't know wtf wmp meant either.<br>
<br>
There are certain High Beggar Zones... Steamfont, Greater Faydark, EC, the Oasis.  Steamfont seems particularly bad.  Luckily I don't go there often.<br>
<br>
Beggars generally get a simple &quot;no&quot; from me or are ignored entirely.  Once I was afk in the nexus and some naked newbie wiz was trying to get my attention for 10 minutes (I looked at my scrollback) for a sow.  Um, hello?  You could've walked to where you wanted to go in that time.  In the end he stood right over me and kept casting spells and interrupting himself to make noise thinking it would get my attention.  WTF???  What is wrong with people?  Either I'm really afk or I'm ignoring you... either way thees no point pressing the issue.<br>
